<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870804-0029 </DOCNO><HL> Toll-Free Number Is Set UpBy Organizers of THA Test</HL><DD> 08/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PHARMACEUTICALS, HOSPITAL SUPPLIES, MANAGEMENT (PHA) </IN><TEXT>   The organizers of the THA test have set up a toll-free number to handle calls from those interested in more information about the drug, the study or the disease. For callers throughout the U.S., except Illinois, the number is (800) 621-0379. For callers in Illinois, the number is (800) 572-6037. The phone calls will be staffed by the Alzheimer's Disease and Related Disorders Association in Chicago.    (See: &quot;Medical Move: A Psychiatrist's Work Leads to a U.S. Study Of Alzheimer's Drug --- But Dr. Summers Shuns Test, Seeks to Widen His Own; Is Memory Really Aided? --- The Fee-for-Research Furor&quot; --- WSJ Aug. 4, 1987) </TEXT></DOC>